Sparrowhawk,<br><br>
Dealing with the VA is an involved process. They have their rules, and they stick with them. In that way they are predictable and honest. The rules are just bizarre.<br><br>
In my situation, I deal with the National Center for PTSD at the Boston VA. There isn't much higher you can go for PTSD care in the VA. I will endure anything to fix this thing in my head. It's me or it, and I have not the slightest thought of giving up.<br><br>
I guess it comes down to personal choice, like so many other things. Speaking of choices, PTSD artificially narrows them down, so you are really boxed in. The most begign things become obstacles, and what others are frightened of, you zip right through.<br><br>
I guess I have said all I can on this thread for a while. I hope that my words provided some insight. SW was particularly intense, and even I was a little shook. He hits the mark, though, every time. He has a way with that. 
